\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 26. A. sardoa} Sprengel, {\i Syst. Veg.}{\b  4}({\b 2}): 127 (1827). Dwarf shrub. Leaves acute or subacute, glabrous or puberulent, dimorphic; outer 25-30 × 2-4 mm, wider than scapes, linear to linear-lanceolate, flat; inner up to 40 × 1-1·2 mm, linear, some what convolute or canaliculate. Scapes 15-30 cm. Sheath shorter than capitulum. Capitula up to 15 mm wide, becoming hard in fruit; involucral bracts mucronulate or muticous- outer half as long as the inner, acuminate, subobtuse or acute, with narrow scarious margins; inner subobtuse, with wide scarious margins. Spikelets sessile or subsessile- bract as long as calyx. Calyx 5-6 mm; tube hirsute on ribs; awns 0·3-0·8 mm. Corolla pale pinkish to purple. 2n = 18.{\i  Mountain pastures and rocks. • Sardegna.} Sa.
\par

