\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 30. A. juniperifolia} (Vahl) Hoffmanns. & Link,{\i  Fl. Port.}{\b  1:} 442 (1813-1820) ({\i A. cespitosa} (Cav.) Boiss.). Dwarf shrub; stock much-branched. Leaves 4-15(-20) × 0·7-1 mm, linear, acute, white-pungent-mucronate, ciliate, puberulent on midrib, flat above but triquetrous. Scapes 0·6-2·5(-5) cm. Sheath 3-9 mm. Capitula 10-14(-17) mm wide; outer involucral bracts shorter than the inner, acuminate, mucronate or cuspidate, with narrow scarious margins; inner mucronulate or muticous, with wide scarious margins. Spikelets sessile; bract as long as calyx; bracteoles absent or very small. Calyx 5-6·5 mm; tube hirsute on ribs; awns 1 mm. Corolla pale purplish or pink. 2n = 18.{\i  Mountain pastures and rock-crevices; calcifuge. •  C. Spain.} Hs.
\par

